<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1437,258,393]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,258,284]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Comments:</emphasis>
We recorded a single female of 
<taxonomicName box="[643,750,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Scaphura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[643,750,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Scaphura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that could not be safely identified as any species of the genus. Additional sampling is required to better understand if this is a new species or simply variation within an already described species.
</paragraph>
